Package: stppSim
Type: Package
Title: Spatial and Temporal Point Patterns Simulation for Social Science Research
Version: 1.0.0
Author: Monsuru Adepeju [cre, aut], 
  Meng Le Zhang [aut]
Maintainer: Monsuru Adepeju <monsuur2010@yahoo.com>
Description: Generates artificial spatio-temporal point patterns (stpp) through the 
  integration of microsimulation and agent-based models. Allows a user to 
  define the behavioural properties of a "walker" (an agent) within a spatially configured 
  environment. The interaction of a walker (such as, a human offender in a crime application, 
  a foraging animal in a Wildlife study, or a carrier in an epidemiological study) with
  it's environment results in new event cases, whose spatiotemporal (ST) signatures
  are measurable at the global level for ST model testing and evaluation.
Language: en-US
License: GPL-3
URL: https://github.com/MAnalytics/stppSim
